ANC president Cyril Ramaphosa addresses supporters in Polokwane.  eNCA MPUMALANGA - ANC President Cyril Ramaphosa is expected to visit the ANC in Mpumalanga this week to engage the party's structures. Political analyst Professor Barry Hanyane says as someone who stands for unity, Ramaphosa must roll the dice carefully and avoid alienating some members in the province. Meanwhile, Mpumalanga ANC insists that all is in order for its elective conference next week, despite the disbanding of the executive committee in the province. As the Mpumalanga ANC prepares for its provincial elective conference, it is awaiting a meeting with party President Cyril Ramaphosa today. The ANC in that province disbanded its Provincial Executive Committee last week. #SouthAfricanMorning #DStv403 pic.twitter.com/gejOvsxXaE